- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper deals with the problem of compressing information (i.e., approximating frequency moments) with limited space. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper discusses lower bounds for the problem of approximating frequency moments. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category as the paper deals with combinatorial problems related to counting and summing frequencies. 
- cs.AL (Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper proposes an algorithm for approximating frequency moments.
